repo.description: A minecraft server written in node.js, modularized
repo.name: flying-squid

body:
Added /setblock (supports relative like /setblock ~ ~-1 ~ 20)

Also added serv.setBlock (prob needs a better name). Sets to world (setBlockType) and sends setBlock to all players (which writes it to the client).

comment_data.body: what is [['','x', 'y', 'z'][i]] ? what is that line trying to achieve ?
what is this ? what is it trying to do ?

commit.message: Added serv.setBlock (sets for all players), player.setBlock (sets locally and not saved to world). Added a test /setblock command with relative coordinates
Changed setBlock to sendBlock, updated API

title: Add setBlock to API and /setblock command
